<item>
            <title>[LU-15979] writing client eviction due to mds failover</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15979</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is another scenario for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12347&quot; title=&quot;lustre write: do not enqueue rpc holding osc/mdc ldlm lock held&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12347&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12347&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; not covered by &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/44151&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/44151&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;    cl_io_loop
      cl_io_lock                    &amp;lt;- ldlm lock is taken here
      cl_io_start
        vvp_io_write_start
        ...
          __generic_file_aio_write
            file_remove_privs
              security_inode_need_killpriv
              ...
                ll_xattr_get_common
                ...
                  mdc_intent_lock   &amp;lt;- enqueue rpc is sent here
      cl_io_unlock                  &amp;lt;- ldlm lock is released

    If enqueue rpc is delayed, the client may get evicted as not
    cancelling lock taken in cl_io_lock.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
